                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As a young chanter I learned to stay as far away from melee as possible, that charming can get you killed, and that melee classes should do the pulling.
<br />

<br />
Now I am paying the price of having a low defense skill from not meleeing, so I get some melee in when its safe to do so.
<br />

<br />
I have since learned that charming is not as tough as I had thought if I have the right strategy, and love to use charm now.
<br />

<br />
But as far as pulling goes, I have only recently considered this an option after reading several posts here.  I am currently level 55 and I would like to know what the benefits are of having the chanter pull, and how does a chanter new at this sort of thing get it done safely?
<br />

<br />
So please, all you brave chanters out there who pull, how is this done?
<br />

<br />
Thank you.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Sleet
<br />
High Elf Enchanter
<br />
Survivors of the Minion
<br />
Tholuxe Paells</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
