                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The beauty of a chanter pulling?
<br />

<br />
We can split as well as anyone and just as fast (and much faster than FD which can take for ever). At 55, you would only really shine in LDoN or old world zones (tier 1 pop just doesnt require it as its easier to mez the rare adds). Your ST Paci is only up to 55 and AoE (WoT..this is LoS where ST paci is not) is up to 60 level mobs. Survey the area, pacify your way around (generally best to start closest too you for if you are resisted and it causes aggro...well you can pull the entire room if you start on far side.
<br />

<br />
Our pulling generally involved drawing decent aggro which is great for warrior MTs (gives them an extra head start). Depending on what your pulling and how resists are, you can either pull with tash, slow, or even a dispell (good if caster is around and recommended if thats the case). Now, I am not sure how dispell works, if it removes paci or not, if it does, make sure surrounding mobs do have it. If slow is sticking, I would pull with that but if resists are high, then tash is the best approach. Slow is the only spell that is really required to get on quickly. Other casters shouldnt be DD'n or DoT'n right away if they know how to control aggro, so you can hold of on tash till before they begin.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Some small tips...
<br />

<br />
- As stated above, regular, single-target pacify line is not LoS. So if you are peeking around a corner just start targeting the edge of the corner (helps if you target yourself first) and if a mob is there, should target him. I used this alot when splitting the front left mob in the hole pre-revamp. Can also use F9 to go to third person view and try to scan sides. Can move back to cast.
<br />

<br />
- In PoP, tash then slow; In LDoN/Old World, depending on cons, you might/should be able to get away with slow and a later tash depending.
<br />

<br />
- Your Level 24 slow is so very nice. Picked up using it on these here boards and use it in LDoN if Im in charge of slows (though I usually try to have a beast to do slows). In PoP, might still want to stick with your best.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The above is fairly general and Im sure someone will come fill in better details, but hope this gives you a start. 
<br />

<br />
Note: I havent pulled in PoP (only 60 and duo with a ranger) and I normally paci in LDoN but havent gotten into completely pullin (usually let the beasty I bring pull with slow...since I give them that responsibility).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=583742" target="_blank" class="postlink">Phreza Bum</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
