                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as pulling when you're level 55 goes, I can only restate what you probably already know; make sure you have high charisma so that when you paci the mobs and it makes it's MR resist, that you don't fail the CHA check to see if it comes after you. You'll probably be grouping in PoP, LoY or LDoN (redundant statement, but just to have it said...), so obviously the zone you're in will dictate the appropriate pulling proceedures. Use paci as much as you can, and pull with your least aggro gaining spell, so that when the tank has to peel the mob off of you, there won't be a beat-down-on-that-dumbass-chanter period that you'd have to suffer throug if you pull with tash. And being sub-61, you wouldn't have benefit of Arcane Rune to save your bacon while the tank grabs aggro.
<br />

<br />
Now, post 61 I can talk about, cuz I love pulling for my groups in BoT or HoH, or wherever my little booties lead me. Generally speaking, the best meathod is to paci the mobs surrounding your intended target with Pacification, then (and here's the secret) pull with Boggle. I learned this trick right here in a guide by Veneficus Grieg. All the tank has to do is sneeze on the mob and it will forget you ever existed. That's pretty much it, up to tier 3. I have no clue about pulling for elemental planes, but I can only assume that they follow a similar pattern.
<br />

<br />
So, to sum up; Paci, Boggle (substitute lowest aggro spell here). Wash, rinse and repeat. It's just that simple. Have your tanks assist you, then of by some strange reason you get an add or two, mez them as needed, but the tanks MUST start off with the mob you originally had targetted when you made the pull, or stuff will get fubar'ed real fast. 
<br />

<br />
So, there's my input. Any corrections or additions, lemme know so I can improve my game.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=206467" target="_blank" class="postlink">Quinthalas Aurothonon</a>
<br />
65 Enchanter
<br />
Bristlebane
