                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">my favourite place to pull was always velks - stand up at the top (frenzy spawn) & look over the edge.  With a Supple Scale Bracer tash would reach the ground floor.  Then as mobs got near maz them as they arrived, slow & wait for the rest of the group to sort out the one they are killing.  This way the group always had a ready supply of things to kill.
<br />

<br />
Advantage of tash pulling was that mez was rarely resisted, however when it was a quick stun gave you space to get the next one off.
<br />

<br />
Still do it now in LDoN if the group are going slowly except I tend to pull with slow & then mez (WoM in place of stun) so that AR lasts a little longer!</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96863" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hardy - Coercer of Povar</a>
<br />
