                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In LDON groups, I pull unless I'm feeling horribly under performance at the time (at which point I'm usually offline or doing something else anyway).
<br />

<br />
The basics have been said above, and they're all dead on.  When you pull, the group kill rate almost never drops (only when you have to move as a group, really).  I've seen 51-54 groups trash a kill 56 mob mission in 46 mintues.  That kill rate would have never happened if someone else had been pulling.
<br />

<br />
Pacify, Tash, Slow, and Mez are your closest allies, along with a healer that knows what you're doing and what to expect.
<br />

<br />
Runing yourself if you don't completely trust your healer or if you feel your hp are lacking is a good idea as well.  Though if you don't trust your healer, you may prefer to let someone else pull.
<br />

<br />
Slow - As mentioned, stick to the 24 slow.  That's all you need when mobs die so fast and there's no time to med.  Even once you're 65, it's more mana efficient than Forlorn and even with ToT *and* ST up, you'll end up with mana problems as a puller.
<br />

<br />
I'm a strong advocate of charm, but it doesn't have a place in all LDON groups.  There are some groups where it will work great and in others it just isn't worth it.  If you fear for the dps of your group, try to keep something charmed, though.
<br />

<br />
Defense skillups will come, they'll just take time.  Depending on how low you are, you may want to get someone with a pet that cons blue to you and go into a duel.  Have their pet hit you for a while and then back off so you can heal/regen up.  Once back up to full, rinse and repeat.  You should max out defense in no time.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
