                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Our pulling generally involved drawing decent aggro which is great for warrior MTs (gives them an extra head start).</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
OK, I've seen in a few places statements along these lines--that an enchanter needs to *jack up* their own aggro and that will help the tank hold aggro.  Maybe it's because I don't play a tank, but for the life of me I haven't been able to figure this one out...obviously I am mis-understanding how aggro and taunt work.  How can one character having huge amounts of aggro help another character get aggro?  Can someone explain this to me in simple terms so I get it?  <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://home.att.ne.jp/apple/dmolden/screenshots/pixcol.gif" border="0" />
