                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Another solution is always to root the mob (provided it can be rooted). Then you can weed out competent melees by seeing who understands max melee and distance aggro  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> .
<br />

<br />
In case of future questions...
<br />

<br />
max melee - furthest distance from a mob that you can successfully attack it.
<br />

<br />
distance aggro is generally associated with root...where mob automatically cues on the closest person on its aggro list thus why melees need to understand max melee.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=583742" target="_blank" class="postlink">Phreza Bum</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
