                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I actually prefer pulling with Recant Magic in LDoN and in BoT.  It has the same affect as Boggle (IE...1 pt of agro..probably a bit more than 1 but not much), it's mana cost is significantly lower than Boggle (250 for boggle, 90 for Recant), and it has the added benifit of stripping any buffs of DS"s that the mobs have.  
<br />

<br />
My typical LDoN pull now is to paci everything but one or two, recant, then run PAST the main tank.  When the mobs come into the camp, they immediatly agro the melee / healers (whoever they come to first in the pull path).  Make sure you let the casters / healers know to stay on the "backside" of the group so that melee's get agro.  I try to mez before they actually get to the melee, but if I don't / can't, they wont be pounding on me and it's pretty easy to lock down.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
