                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally for PoP content, I grab mob with tash, run it back to camp, mez before it can hit me, slow, mem flux, wait for engage to make sure mob doesnt go charging after me and then grab another(I always try to have druid wolf form on for perma sow; perma illusion is too cool <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> ); non-stop killing like that. I keep pacify up, but rarely use unless I think I will get more than 3 mobs.. would normally rather just have an add or two and WoM, mezz after the initial distance mezz.... rarely run into a mana problem unless we are just killing insane fast. In LDoN it is a different story and I prefer tank to just charge mobs and I play clean up, seems to work about as well as anything in terms of speed and its not nearly as much of a yawn-fest as paci pulling.
<br />
The exception is hard mode... but then paci doesnt work for crap there anyway and rooting, mezzing, evacing, etc all need to be used sometimes to pull something managable... Anyway, this is how I do things and can't complain so far.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
